The paper is about open-domain question answering, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The paper proposes two models for evidence aggregation to generate answers from multiple passages. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
